3:00-4:00 Card/Gift Shower for Seniors at the Waubay School.

The Governor has closed schools for the remainder of the year; which means students will not return to the school building. School will continue to go on virtually and online. It is imperative that students continue to do the work assigned and maintain contact with teachers. Assignments will continue to be posted on the Google doc on the links below, through Google Classroom, and email. High school students are still earning credit and will need to complete work in order to earn that credit. All activities for the remainder of the school year are cancelled.

span.span: The Mission of the Waubay Schools

p.span: The Waubay School Board and staff believe education is a continuous process of building connections that lead to student successes personally, socially and academically.
Every student in the Waubay School will……
Have the opportunity to learn in a safe, positive and culturally diverse environment.
Have the opportunity to learn the skills to be a respectful, responsible and dependable life-long learner.
Have the opportunity to utilize technology in every day learning.
Have the opportunity to access personal, social and academic guidance throughout his or her educational career.
Have the opportunity to be career and college ready upon completion of graduation requirements.
